page.title: 12AINSDALE NATURE RESERVE 1
page.content: AINSDALE AND THE AREA AROUND IS WELL KNOWN FOR ITS FAUNA AND FLORA.IT HAS MANY RARE PLANTS AND ANIMALS WHICH ARE FOUND IN THE NATURE RESERVE. THE COAST IS SET UP IN SEVERAL STAGES STARTING FROM THE SEA THERE IS THE BEACH,THE MOBILE DUNES,THE FIXED DUNES,MASSAMS SLACK,DAMP SLACK,DRY SLACK AND FINALLY THE PINE WOODS. THE MAIN WILDLIFE ON THE BEACH IS BIRDS.THESE INCLUDE OYSTERCATCHERS,GREAT BLACK BACKED GULL,SANDERLINGS,HERRING GULL AND THE BLACK HEADED GULL.PLENTY OF DEAD ANIMALS AND PLANT REMAINS CAN BE FOUND ALONG THE HIGH TIDE LINE,SUCH AS SKATE EGG CASES(MERMAIDS PURSE),WHELK EGG CASES,SEAMAT AND SEA WORM TUBES WHICH IS A SAND TUBE HELD TO THE WORM BY A STICKY SECRETION.LESS COMMONLY FOUND ALONG THIS LINE ARE SEA MICE AND CUTTLEFISH BONES.
